***** Course Description *****
15.769 Operations Strategy provides a unifying framework for analyzing
strategic issues in manufacturing and service operations. Students analyze the
relationships between manufacturing and service companies and their suppliers,
customers, and competitors. The course covers strategic decisions in
technology, facilities, vertical integration, human resources, and other areas,
and also explores means of competition such as cost, quality, and
innovativeness.
